A second person has died from of a crash involving a Ute that hit several pedestrians on a footpath last month.

The 49-year-old man died in hospital on New Year’s Eve resulting from injuries he sustained when the uts struck him and a woman on Victoria Road, Rozelle.

Police say the 22-year-old P-plater veered off the road, when his white Holden Commodore ute mounted the curb and hit the pedestrians on December 14.

